77 A.3d 1048 ATTORNEY GRIEVANCE COMMISSION OF MARYLAND, Petitioner v. Steven Mark VOGELHUT, Respondent. Misc. Docket AG No. 55,

Sept. Term, 2013.

Court of Appeals of Maryland. Oct. 17, 2013.

ORDER

The Court of Appeals of Maryland, having considered the Joint Petition of the Attorney Grievance Commission and Respondent Steven Mark Vogelhut, to replace Respondent on Inactive Status By Consent pursuant to Maryland Rule 16-772, it is this 17th day of October, 2013;

ORDERED, that the Joint Petition be, and it is hereby GRANTED, and the Respondent, Steven Mark Vogelhut is hereby placed on Inactive Status by consent; and it is further,

ORDERED, that the Clerk of this Court shall remove the name of Steven Mark Vogelhut from the register of attorneys in the Court and certify that fact to the Client Protection Fund of the Bar of Maryland and all Clerks of all judicial tribunals in this State in accordance with Maryland Rule 16-772(d).
